# Band 4 — 🚀 You can LOSE

Here's the thing about winning: it only means something if you could have lost. A game where clicking is always safe is a progress bar with extra steps.

Band 4 installs the lives system — the other half of the game's heart.

## 1. Lives on the state

[`newGame()`](http://localhost:3031/m3-contract) already hands back a state. Now it has to hand back one with **at least 1 life** in it:

```js
function newGame() {
  return { score: 0, lives: 3 };
}
```

Three is the classic. One life is brutal. Five is friendly. Your game, your cruelty setting.

## 2. `loseLife(state)` — exactly one

```js
function loseLife(state) {
  state.lives = state.lives - 1;
  return state;
}
```

**Exactly one.** The checker compares your result against a fresh game's lives minus one, so `- 2` fails and forgetting [`return state`](http://localhost:3031/m3-band2) fails.

## 3. `isOver(state)` — the ending

```js
function isOver(state) {
  return state.lives <= 0;
}
```

The checker tests both sides: [`true`](http://localhost:3031/d13-else) for `{ score: 0, lives: 0 }`, `false` for a brand new game. Use [`<= 0`](http://localhost:3031/m3-band4) rather than `=== 0` — if a bug ever drops lives to `-1`, `<= 0` still ends the run instead of letting a ghost keep playing.

## 4. Wire the danger in

This is where the three functions become a *game*. Somewhere in your browser block, a click has to be able to go **badly**:

```js
if (roll > monster.danger) {
  addScore(state, monster.points);          // good outcome
} else {
  loseLife(state);                          // bad outcome — that's the danger
}

if (hasWon(state)) {
  // 🏆 victory message
} else if (isOver(state)) {
  // 💀 game over message — and stop the play buttons from working
}
```

The checker requires your browser block to **actually call `isOver`** — declaring the function and never using it doesn't count. And when the run ends, *end it*: `attackButton.disabled = true;` so nobody can keep scoring on a corpse. Your restart button has to bring the buttons back (`disabled = false`) along with the score and the lives.

Show the lives on the page too — `❤️❤️❤️` shrinking is worth ten paragraphs of instructions.

> 🤔 **Why this is Level 4:** you've built a complete game loop — state, actions, win check, lose check, reset. That's the same skeleton under every game ever shipped. From here you're not learning what a game is anymore, you're just deciding what yours is about.

